---+++How do you change links and information on the page http://www.tdwg.org/activities/? 
d8 19
a26 17
_Lee's Solution_

   1. Log on to the Typo3 backend (http://www.tdwg.org/typo3)
   1. Click the "List" menu on the left-hand side
   1. Click the item "Front-end Users" on the website tree (after the Homepage and before TDWG2006)
   1. Scroll the contents panel all the way down to the "Search String" field, type Literature and click "Search"
   1. Click on the pencil icon near the item "Literature Interest Group" under the list of Website Usergroups.
   1. Click Edit in the pop-up
   1. Change the Wiki field accordingly.
   1. Click the "save" button.

---+++How is access handled (e.g., Conveners editing their group's pages)?

   1. Open Typo3, click List, then browse to the root of the page tree (called TDWG, near an little Earth icon). All registered users have a Typo3 backend account (listed under Backend user), but only a few have that account enabled. Only the 20 first users are listed at once, so you'll see on the second page of Backend users that AnnaWeitzman has a backend account (the icon next to her name is blue and not grayed out).
   1. To let someone in, first you need to locate them on that list by using the search field all the way at the bottom of the page. 
   1. Then you click the pencil icon and enable their backend account by unchecking the disable flag at the bottom of the form.
   1. Then you need to let them know they can access the backend at http://www.tdwg.org/typo3. They should use the same credentials they use everywhere on the site.
@


