   1. Open Typo3, click List, then browse to the root of the page tree (called TDWG, near an little Earth icon). All registered users have a Typo3 backend account (listed under Backend user), but only a few have that account enabled. Only the 20 first users are listed at once, so you'll see that AlexChapman has a backend account (the icon next to his name is blue and not grayed out).
   1. To let someone in, first you need to locate them on that list by using the search field all the way at the bottom of the page. Then you click the pencil icon and enable their backend account by unchecking the disable flag at the bottom of the form.
